summary: I am so weak for 'characters watch and react to the future' fics. Those stories can be so interesting and cool if the author is...
body:
I am so weak for ‘characters watch and react to the future’ fics. Those stories can be so interesting and cool if the author is good and proper time and effort are put into them, but it’s also the fucking worst, cause they get through maybe three episodes before

A) the author gives up on the story and it’s never updated again

B) the little bastards that go trolling for those fics harass the author with copyright rules until the story is deleted

C) to avoid B, the author cuts out the sections detailing the movie/show being watched, leaving the reader to just guess which part the characters are actually reacting to and hoping for the best

summary: [Spoilers] Whats the leading theory on this??
title: [Spoilers] Whats the leading theory on this??
body:
What is the leading theory on what happens when Dany and Jon find out about Jon’s identity? I’ve heard a lot of people think that they will rule as king and queen but differing on which one will stake their Claim.

It’s occurred to me, thought, that they might completely stop their romance due to it being incest. What happens then? Still side by side, or possibly against? Does Jon just keep quiet and let her stake her claim?

Thoughts please

Side thought: all the queens in the story are (possibly) down with incest.



Source: https://ift.tt/2Nq7xZH

title: Adaptation vidéoludique de livres
body: Parmi les livres les plus populaires, on peut citer l’adaptation vidéoludique de Game of Thrones, Le Seigneur des Anneaux et Harry Potter. Cependant, certaines œuvres littéraires moins connues ont également leur jeu vidéo, comme Les Piliers de la Terre et Sherlock Holmes.
